https://letskodeit.teachable.com/


Parent
    Syntax: xpath-to-some-element//parent::<tag>
Preceding Sibling
    Syntax: xpath-to-some-element//preceding-sibling::<tag>
Following Sibling
    Syntax: xpath-to-some-element//following-sibling::<tag>


To find the parent tag of anchor tag (a)
    //a[@href='/sign_in']//parent::li

To find the preceding sibling
    //a[@href='/sign_in']//parent::li//preceding-sibling::li

To find the following sibling
    //a[@href='/sign_in']//parent::li//preceding-sibling::li//following-sibling::li
        we will find 2 nodes here
        use brackets or array (wc doesnt start in zero)

        //a[@href='/sign_in']//parent::li//preceding-sibling::li//following-sibling::li[1]
